# C Cheet Sheet

<b-row>

<b-col>

## Basic Structure

```c
pre-processor directives
global declarations

int main()
{
    local deceleration
    statement sequences
    return 0;
}
```

## Input / Output
```c
int k1, k2;
char c, s[100];
scanf("%d%d", &k1, &k2);
scanf(" %c", &c);
scanf("%s", s);
```

## Function
```c
int f(int n);

int main()
{
    // statements
    int k = f(3);
    // statements
}
```

</b-col>
<b-col>

## Branch
```c
if (c) { statements }
if (c) {
    // statements
} else {
    // statements
}

if (c1) {
    // statements
} else if (c2) {
    // statements
} else { 
    // statements
}
```

## Loop
```c
while (c) {
    // statements
}

do {
    // statements
} while (c);

for (c1; c2; c3) {
    // statements
}
```

</b-col>
<b-col>

## Structure
```c
struct sName {
    int x;
    int y;
};
struct sName s1, s2;

typedef struct sName newType;
newType s3;
```

## Pointer
```c
int x = 5;
int *y = &x;

int a[8] = {0};
int *ap;

for (int i=0; i<8; i++) {
    scanf("%d", a+i);
}

for (ap=a; ap<a+8; ap++) {
    printf("%d ", *ap);
}
```

